# Research Notes

I started this project knowing nothing about post-quantum cryptography. 
The first thing that surprised me was how different the three algorithms 
feel when you actually run them. Kyber is fast. Dilithium is unpredictable. 
SLH-DSA is painfully slow but has the tiniest public keys.

The variance finding came by accident. I noticed my ML-KEM numbers 
kept changing between runs but my ML-DSA signing numbers stayed 
consistently high no matter what I did. That is when I realized they 
are different kinds of variance entirely.

I am 16 years old and taught myself Python and cryptography to do this 
research. All benchmark code is written by me. The research took about 
3 months from zero knowledge to this dataset.
